text: Trying to present it as a societal issue is a bit misleading because no one voted for any of it. It was opposed and protested on every step of the way by the people and migration was still forced top-down in spite of everyone's wishes. Riots over it were suppressed by the police.

It's similar to how no one in the USA voted for not having a Southern border and deportation of illegal migrants is still the most popular bipartisan issue, but no one gets it done. No one ever actually wanted or voted for letting third world migrants into Europe.

The "meaning" of life is going to Divine Liturgy once a week and receiving the Eucharist. People want something that sounds more zany or poetic but really this is the centre of it all. Nothing else will matter or "mean" to us as much as participating in Orthodox sacramental life.
The importance of the Eucharist is so radical that its effects extend even to our dead family members who receive the grace from our communion too. Everything else is just preparation for it.
